<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-10-04T14:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-10-04T14:45:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">717.2114/53: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Munro</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-10-04T14:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            4, 1927—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 5:15
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>260. Department’s May [<hi rend="italic">September</hi>] 14, 5 p.m.
                                The President asked me today to ascertain when the Department would
                                be ready to express an opinion regarding the San Andrés Archipelago
                                question.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Munro</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>